OL,3,GNEWSCLabour MPs warn of voter backlash
OL,4,Cover terrestrial TV switch-off
OL,5,
OL,6,FA group of Labour MPs has warned the
OL,7,FPrime Minister that pressing ahead with
OL,8,Fplans to switch off terrestrial
OL,9,Ftelevision could cost the party seats
OL,10,Fat the next election, according to The
OL,11,Fi Paper.
OL,13,FIn an open letter seen by the paper, 17
OL,14,FMPs from across the party ` including a
OL,15,Fclose ally of Wes Streeting ` caution
OL,16,Fthat ending the Freeview service,
OL,17,Fcurrently relied upon by around 10
OL,18,Fmillion homes, risks alienating voters
OL,19,Fwho cannot afford to replace it.
OL,23,EPub: 07-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,156,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15502
SC,0002
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F155A1784144490
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWSCLabour MPs warn of voter backlash
OL,4,Cover terrestrial TV switch-off
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe letter argues that those most
OL,7,Fdependent on terrestrial TV tend to be
OL,8,Folder, female, on lower incomes, and
OL,9,Fconcentrated in the towns and coastal
OL,10,Fcommunities where Labour's majorities
OL,11,Fare thinnest.
OL,13,FRequiring such households to take out a
OL,14,Fbroadband contract simply to keep
OL,15,Fwatching the television they already
OL,16,Freceive, the MPs write, amounts not to
OL,17,Fa transition but to a charge ` and one
OL,18,Fthat voters will recognise as such.
OL,23,EPub: 07-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,156,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15503
SC,0003
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F155A1784144490
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWSCLabour MPs warn of voter backlash
OL,4,Cover terrestrial TV switch-off
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe intervention follows expectations
OL,7,Fthat Culture Secretary Lisa Nandy will
OL,8,Fapprove the BBC-backed plan to retire
OL,9,FFreeview as viewing shifts online.
OL,11,FSuch a move would remove access to more
OL,12,Fthan 70 standard channels and over 10
OL,13,Fin HD ` among them BBC One, BBC Two,
OL,14,FITV 1/STV, Channel 4 and 5 ` delivered
OL,15,Fvia Digital Terrestrial Television.
OL,23,EPub: 07-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,156,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15504
SC,0004
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F155A1784144490
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWSCLabour MPs warn of voter backlash
OL,4,Cover terrestrial TV switch-off
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe signatories, who include Cat Smith,
OL,7,FLuke Akehurst, Sarah Champion, Lorraine
OL,8,FBeavers and Joe Morris ` the latter a
OL,9,FStreeting ally who resigned as his
OL,10,Fparliamentary aide ` are urging
OL,11,Fministers to use a forthcoming Green
OL,12,FPaper to guarantee terrestrial
OL,13,Fbroadcasting beyond its current 2034
OL,14,Fprotection and well into the 2040s.
OL,16,FOne estimate cited by the paper
OL,17,Fsuggests the change could add around
OL,18,F#200 to some households' bills through
OL,19,Fbroadband charges.
OL,21,FThe Government insists no-one will be
OL,22,Fleft behind.
OL,23,EPub: 07-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,156,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15505
SC,0005
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F155A1784144490
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GNEWSCLabour MPs warn of voter backlash
OL,4,Cover terrestrial TV switch-off
OL,5,
OL,6,FA spokesperson for the Department for
OL,7,FCulture, Media and Sport said work was
OL,8,Funder way across the sector on a
OL,9,Flong-term, sustainable approach to TV
OL,10,Fdistribution, with a decision on
OL,11,Fwhether to extend the 2034 commitment
OL,12,Fto follow as soon as possible.
OL,14,FThe i Paper understands that, rather
OL,15,Fthan fix a switch-off date, ministers
OL,16,Fwill consult on a range of options,
OL,17,Fwith any change dependent on universal
OL,18,Faccess to affordable superfast
OL,19,Fbroadband.
OL,23,EPub: 07-Jun-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
